    public interface Disposable
    A disposable is an object that can be explicitly destroyed to release their internal resources.
    Author:
    Raymond L. Rivera

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void notifyDispose()
      Explicitly releases the internal resources held by this instance, making it unusable afterwards.

    • Method Detail

      • notifyDispose

        void notifyDispose()
        Explicitly releases the internal resources held by this instance, making it unusable afterwards.

        WARNING: This method is meant to be used internally by the framework and not by game clients. Use directly only if you really know what you're doing.
